-{"id":"bd-j9jo3.9.5","title":"robot-redesign/validation: remove legacy robot assembly paths and dead code","description":"Delete or replace the obsolete assembly paths, duplicate renderers, and dead legacy scaffolding that become unnecessary after the redesign is in place. This task exists because leaving the old paths around would preserve exactly the ambiguity and drift this plan is meant to fix.","design":"The cleanup should remove duplicated surface assembly logic, stale helpers that bypass the shared projection model, and discovery code that no longer reflects reality. It should only proceed after unit, integration, benchmark, and E2E coverage are green and docs/examples clearly identify the new path as authoritative.\n\nThe goal is not aesthetic tidiness; it is preventing future contributors from accidentally reviving the wrong architecture.","acceptance_criteria":"This task is complete when the old robot assembly paths are no longer active or misleading, the new path is the one obvious way to build robot outputs, and the automated unit, integration, benchmark, E2E, docs, and example stack points only at the new architecture.","notes":"Cleanup is part of the architecture work, not an optional polish pass.","status":"in_progress","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","estimated_minutes":180,"created_at":"2026-03-21T23:38:30.465593071Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-26T22:22:12.564744919Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["cleanup","robot-redesign","validation"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.9.5","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.9","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-21T23:38:30.465593071Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.9.5","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.9.1","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-21T23:38:37.522173878Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.9.5","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.9.10","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-